President Cyril Ramaphosa. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - South Africa is committed to fighting climate change, according to President Cyril Ramaphosa. Ramaphosa says the country will meet its international obligations. READ: All countries must get COVID-19 vaccine: Ramaphosa "We have done some work and we have seen success with industrial symbiosis initiatives, where one sector's waste can be used and its precious input into another sector. "We are developing ambitious producer responsibility schemes in the industry to manage waste effectively," he said. Ramaphosa was speaking on day two of the G20 Leaders’ Summit which is being facilitated by the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.